    Scope and Contents
Papers of Clarence Danhof, Professor of Political Economy, 1972-82, and Associate Dean of Organization and Management Studies 1972-82, include outgoing correspondence from Danhof to University faculty and administrators concerning administrative, curricular, and student affairs.  Also includes newsclippings, publications, budgets, maps, memoranda and other collected research material concerning Danhof's research on  Springfield's urban development, government and public services, "Case Studies of Urban Government."  
  
